125
00:04:31,421 --> 00:04:33,688
and the nurses are like,
"Doesn't she look fat?"

126
00:04:33,757 --> 00:04:36,657
And I'm like, "No, she
looks like a naked mole rat."

127
00:04:36,727 --> 00:04:38,993
And my doctor got
nominated for some prize,

128
00:04:39,062 --> 00:04:40,239
and everyone's really jealous.

129
00:04:40,263 --> 00:04:41,329
That's cool.

130
00:04:42,065 --> 00:04:43,682
Not as cool as that.

131
00:04:43,751 --> 00:04:45,016
Yeah.

132
00:04:45,085 --> 00:04:46,246
My parents try to
distract me from the fact

133
00:04:46,270 --> 00:04:47,536
that I'm trapped in a bubble.

134
00:04:47,604 --> 00:04:49,249
Well, aren't you getting
some test results back today

135
00:04:49,273 --> 00:04:50,472
that are gonna get you out?

136
00:04:50,541 --> 00:04:51,806
Yeah.

137
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:53,452
Here they come. Come visit me.

138
00:04:53,476 --> 00:04:55,610
My brother's room is
end of the hall on the right.

139
00:04:56,713 --> 00:04:58,012
Well, there he is.

140
00:04:58,081 --> 00:04:59,180
Hey, Brady bug.

141
00:04:59,249 --> 00:05:00,281
Braden.

142
00:05:00,350 --> 00:05:01,594
Up high, champ. Hi, baby.

143
00:05:01,618 --> 00:05:03,751
Mom, why are you crying?

144
00:05:03,820 --> 00:05:04,920
Oh, I'm...

145
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:06,854
I'm not.

146
00:05:09,009 --> 00:05:10,442
I'm sorry. I can't.

147
00:05:13,614 --> 00:05:17,198
Unfortunately, your
T-cell count is still zero.

148
00:05:17,267 --> 00:05:18,666
Your infection
is almost cleared,

149
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:20,747
but we were hoping for
your T cell count to respond.

150
00:05:20,771 --> 00:05:22,036
I get it.

151
00:05:22,105 --> 00:05:24,606
But I don't understand
why my mom's crying.

152
00:05:24,674 --> 00:05:26,974
There's got to be other
stuff you guys can try.

153
00:05:27,043 --> 00:05:29,905
You're not gonna make me live
in this bubble for the rest of my life.

154
00:05:29,929 --> 00:05:31,429
Dad?

155
00:05:31,498 --> 00:05:32,930
It's not so simple, bud.

156
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:36,001
Your body has no
ability to fight infection,

157
00:05:36,069 --> 00:05:38,436
and the enzyme's
not working anymore.

158
00:05:38,505 --> 00:05:40,905
Bone-marrow transplants in
kids with SCID can be effective,

159
00:05:40,974 --> 00:05:42,474
so we're still
looking for a match.

160
00:05:42,542 --> 00:05:44,487
They've been looking for a
match for me since I was a baby,

161
00:05:44,511 --> 00:05:45,554
and they haven't found one.

162
00:05:45,578 --> 00:05:46,818
What if you still can't?

163
00:05:50,334 --> 00:05:53,284
No other treatment
for your disease exists.

164
00:05:53,354 --> 00:05:58,122
We're working on it,
but for the time being,

165
00:05:58,191 --> 00:06:01,092
your only safe place
is right where you are.

166
00:06:07,735 --> 00:06:09,334
Hey, Frankie. You're late.

167
00:06:09,403 --> 00:06:11,715
I'm not a patient anymore,
so I don't have to be at rounds.

168
00:06:11,739 --> 00:06:13,037
But you do.

169
00:06:13,106 --> 00:06:14,346
You're right. I'm late.

170
00:06:14,375 --> 00:06:16,140
Want to race? Yeah. Come on.

171
00:06:17,327 --> 00:06:18,960
I got you! Come on! Come on!

172
00:06:19,029 --> 00:06:20,273
Hey, hey! Slow down!

173
00:06:20,297 --> 00:06:21,930
That's not fair! Come on!

174
00:06:24,835 --> 00:06:25,917
Hey, Linkie.

175
00:06:25,985 --> 00:06:27,196
I got you a
chocolate chip muffin

176
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:28,364
for when you're feeling better.

177
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:29,748
Well, how are you
feeling, Frankie?

178
00:06:29,772 --> 00:06:31,284
Pretty good. She just
beat me in a race, so...

179
00:06:31,308 --> 00:06:34,142
Looks like that pacemaker
I put in is working.

180
00:06:34,211 --> 00:06:35,243
And...

181
00:06:35,312 --> 00:06:36,961
Seriously, Ivy.

182
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:38,710
Sour-cream-and-onion
chips for breakfast?

183
00:06:38,765 --> 00:06:40,426
You said I should put on weight.

184
00:06:40,450 --> 00:06:42,484
Good.

185
00:06:42,552 --> 00:06:44,603
So, two weeks
post-op heart transplant,

186
00:06:44,671 --> 00:06:46,705
and Ivy's indices are excellent.

187
00:06:46,773 --> 00:06:48,189
And Mr. Link?

188
00:06:48,257 --> 00:06:50,336
Lincoln McNeil, age 9,
end-stage heart failure,

189
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:53,561
awaiting transplant, status 1A.

190
00:06:53,630 --> 00:06:55,541
There's a family
history of the disease.

191
00:06:55,565 --> 00:06:57,065
The cause is still unknown.

192
00:06:57,150 --> 00:07:00,063
Link first showed signs of
cardiomyopathy two weeks ago

193
00:07:00,087 --> 00:07:02,353
and has deteriorated rapidly.

194
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:05,340
An attempt to put him
on a Berlin Heart failed...

195
00:07:05,409 --> 00:07:07,020
Due to something
I can't remember.

196
00:07:07,044 --> 00:07:08,109
Clotting.

197
00:07:08,178 --> 00:07:09,322
That's it.

198
00:07:09,346 --> 00:07:12,764
The patient is now
on ECMO and is...

199
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:14,098
Stable.

200
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:16,067
I couldn't have
said it better myself.

201
00:07:16,136 --> 00:07:18,014
Thanks. So, where
are we with UNOS?

202
00:07:18,038 --> 00:07:20,872
Well, Link is at
the top of the list.

203
00:07:20,924 --> 00:07:23,241
How much longer can
he survive on ECMO?

204
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:25,610
Well, with sweep
numbers this low...

205
00:07:26,296 --> 00:07:27,896
At least a week.

206
00:07:28,782 --> 00:07:30,732
So, we pray for a miracle?

207
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,783
We got one with Ivy.

208
00:07:32,852 --> 00:07:35,236
We're not just sitting
around and waiting.

209
00:07:35,305 --> 00:07:37,622
We are aggressively
looking at other options.

210
00:07:39,059 --> 00:07:40,408
In the meantime...

211
00:07:41,644 --> 00:07:43,427
Heart-healthy food, okay?

212
00:07:45,815 --> 00:07:48,183
So, I put a call in to
these guys from Stanford

213
00:07:48,251 --> 00:07:50,919
who are doing animal testing
with a drug-eluting pump

214
00:07:50,987 --> 00:07:52,420
to prevent clotting.

215
00:07:52,488 --> 00:07:55,724
Never been tried on
humans, but Link is a little kid.

216
00:07:55,792 --> 00:07:57,709
The fit might be
right. It could work.

217
00:07:57,778 --> 00:07:59,922
I'll let you guys
know what they say.

218
00:07:59,946 --> 00:08:01,879
So, that's how
you're gonna play this,

219
00:08:01,948 --> 00:08:04,165
act like it's just another
day at the office?

220
00:08:04,234 --> 00:08:05,311
